      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<h2>Enable Mobs</h2><p>When enabled, the <strong>Mobs Average Results</strong> table from the <em>Dungeon Master's Guide (2024),</em> page 82, will be used for attack rolls when all the following conditions are met:</p><ul><li><p>Between <strong>four</strong> and <strong>ten</strong> identical tokens are selected.</p></li><li><p>Only <strong>one</strong> token is targeted.</p></li><li><p>The activity used is an <strong>Attack</strong>.</p></li></ul><p>Instead of rolling an attack, the number of successful hits is calculated using the table and a single damage roll is automatically posted to the chat. You can apply Advantage or Disadvantage by holding the appropriate key modifier when clicking the attack.</p><h2>Use Average Damage</h2><p>When enabled, mobs will deal average damage, otherwise damage wil be rolled instead.</p>"
